LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1203
Introduced by Clouse, 37.
Read first time January 21, 2026
Committee: Government, Military and Veterans Affairs
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to counties; to provide for the treatment of
2 uncashed checks issued by counties as prescribed.
3 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1203 LB1203
2026 2026
1 Section 1. (1) Each county treasurer and county clerk shall
2 maintain a list of checks issued by his or her office that remain
3 uncashed after two years, including the amount of the check and the name
4 of the person to whom the check was issued.
5 (2) Any such check for an amount of less than one hundred dollars
6 shall be void three years after the date of its issuance and shall cease
7 to be an obligation of the county at such time. Such check may thereafter
8 be presented to the county board of such county which may approve the
9 claim for payment.
10 (3) Any check that is void pursuant to subsection (2) of this
11 section shall be charged off upon the books of the county, and the county
12 treasurer shall credit the money, including any interest thereon, to the
13 general fund of such county.
14 (4) Any check that is void pursuant to subsection (2) of this
15 section shall cease to be intangible personal property held for the owner
16 and shall not be subject to the Uniform Disposition of Unclaimed Property
17 Act.
